Data Tidiness Issues

Tidiness issues pertain to the structure of data. These structural problems generally prevent easy analysis. Untidy data is also known as messy data. The requirements for tidy data are:

  • Each variable forms a column.
  • Each observation forms a row.
  • Each type of observational unit forms a table.

There are the only two tidiness issues:

  • merging the three data sets in one
  • combining the columns doggo, puppo, pupper, floofer into a single column

All other are quality issues, please move them to the proper list.

Combine p1, p2 and p3 columns

This is not required as these columns are not values of a single column like dog stages. These columns are individual separate values, they are orderwise prediction of an algorithm and represent the top 3 predictions. So these are fine as separate and no need to merge.

If you want to keep then keep the top prediction values but don't merge them.

Requires Changes

MULTIPLE DOG STAGES

For dog stage, there are some rows with multiple dog stages:


Here is how to clean them:

# handle none
df_clean.doggo.replace('None', '', inplace=True)
df_clean.floofer.replace('None', '', inplace=True)
df_clean.pupper.replace('None', '', inplace=True)
df_clean.puppo.replace('None', '', inplace=True)

# merge into column
df_clean['dog_stage'] = df_clean.doggo + df_clean.floofer + df_clean.pupper + df_clean.puppo

# handle multiple stages
df_clean.loc[df_clean.dog_stage == 'doggopupper', 'dog_stage'] = 'doggo, pupper'
df_clean.loc[df_clean.dog_stage == 'doggopuppo', 'dog_stage'] = 'doggo, puppo'
df_clean.loc[df_clean.dog_stage == 'doggofloofer', 'dog_stage'] = 'doggo, floofer'

# handle missing values
df_clean.loc[df_clean.dog_stage == '', 'dog_stage'] = np.nan

DECIMAL DOG RATINGS

For dog ratings, there are some observations with decimal ratings


Here is how to extract the decimal ratings with regular expressions:

twitter_archive_clean[twitter_archive_clean.text.str.contains(r"(\d+\.\d*\/\d+)")][['text', 'rating_numerator']]
